{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840693974,"sessionID":"ses_287a65705ffeL73ZtVA1QPxGQz","part":{"id":"prt_d785a3860001GL4jqjH5N44Yi1","messageID":"msg_d785a20680011i498PkvALUk7y","sessionID":"ses_287a65705ffeL73ZtVA1QPxGQz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_e8a0a0617d744eb996f49bb7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine shared types, constants, and utility functions in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` module to support the AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs. This includes API group constants, resource identifiers, and common types used across multiple CRDs.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe shared types and constants provide:\n\n- **API group identification**: Consistent GroupName and Version constants for scheme registration\n- **Resource naming**: Standardized plural resource names for Kubernetes API routing\n- **Client-go compatibility**: Types consumed by generated client library\n- **Type safety**: Shared constants prevent hardcoded strings across the codebase\n\nThese shared definitions are consumed by:\n- pkg/apis (type definitions)\n- client-go library (generated client code)\n- Controllers (workload manager reads CRs)\n- Helm CRDs (generated from types)\n\n## Scope\n\n### Deliverables\n\n| Deliverable | Path | Description |\n|-------------|------|-------------|\n| Constants | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | GroupName, Version, SchemeGroupVersion |\n| Resource helpers | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Resource(), AddKnownTypes |\n| Shared types | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | TargetPort, ContainerTemplateSpec, AuthMode, etc. |\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    GroupName = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n    Version   = \"v1alpha1\"\n)\n```\n\n### Resource Identifiers\n\n| Resource | Plural | Short Name | Type |\n|----------|--------|------------|------|\n| AgentRuntime | agentruntimes | ar | AgentRuntime |\n| CodeInterpreter | codeinterpreters | ci | CodeInterpreter |\n\n### Shared Types\n\n| Type | Used By | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| TargetPort | AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter | Port configuration with protocol and path |\n| ContainerTemplateSpec | CodeInterpreter | Simplified container spec |\n| PodTemplateSpec | AgentRuntime | Custom pod template |\n| PodSpec | AgentRuntime | Selective pod spec subset |\n| ContainerSpec | AgentRuntime | Selective container spec |\n| AuthMode | CodeInterpreter | Enum: picod, none |\n\n### Helper Functions\n\n```go\nfunc Resource(resource string) schema.GroupResource\nfunc AddKnownTypes(scheme *runtime.Scheme) error\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Role |\n|------------|---------|------|\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` | ^1.32 | Scheme, runtime.Object, schema |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ^1.32 | metav1 types |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **pkg/apis** — Type definitions reference constants\n2. **client-go** — Generated clients use Resource() for lister registration\n3. **Controllers** — Use constants for scheme registration\n4. **Helm CRDs** — CRD generation relies on kubebuilder markers\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Constant mismatch | High | Single source of truth in register.go |\n| Breaking changes | Medium | v1alpha1 is unstable; reserve v1 for stable |\n| Type duplication | Low | Shared types in types.go, no duplication |\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Define constants per CRD\n\n**Approach**: Define GroupName/Version in each CRD type file.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simple initial implementation\n\n**Cons**:\n- Duplication across files\n- Inconsistent values\n- Harder to maintain\n\n**Decision**: Centralized in register.go.\n\n### Alternative 2: Use string literals directly\n\n**Approach**: Hardcode \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\" and \"v1alpha1\" everywhere.\n\n**Pros**:\n- No additional code\n\n**Cons**:\n- No compile-time validation\n- Error-prone\n- Difficult to refactor\n\n**Decision**: Use constants for type safety.\n\n### Alternative 3: Separate shared package\n\n**Approach**: Create `pkg/apis/runtime/types/common/` for shared types.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Clear separation\n\n**Cons**:\n- Over-engineering for small project\n- More import paths\n- Circular dependency risk\n\n**Decision**: Keep shared types in same package per Kubernetes convention.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n1. Ensure constants in `register.go` match client-go expectations\n2. Verify TargetPort, ContainerTemplateSpec are used by both CRDs\n3. Run `make generate` to produce zz_generated.deepcopy.go\n4. Verify with `make gen-client` ensures client-go compatibility\n5. Verify with `make gen-crd` produces valid CRD YAML\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Constants defined in register.go match API group spec\n- [ ] Shared types (TargetPort, ContainerTemplateSpec) are used by both CRDs\n- [ ] `make generate` succeeds without errors\n- [ ] `make gen-client` succeeds without type errors\n- [ ] Go types compile without errors (`go build ./pkg/apis/...`)","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840693944,"end":1775840693971}}}}
